The paper deals with the analysis of algorithms for solving satisfiability problems, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The use of a cost function to analyze the PPSZ algorithm suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and the analysis of algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the algorithm to satisfiability problems in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) is also possible. Finally, the use of probabilistic methods in the analysis of the algorithm suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
